SIMPLE: easterly
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Easterly
<hw>East"er*ly</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Coming from the
east; <as>as, it was <ex>easterly</ex> wind</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Situated, directed, or moving toward the east;
<as>as, the <ex>easterly</ex> side of a lake; an <ex>easterly</ex>
course or voyage.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Easterly</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Easterly
<hw>East"er*ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>Toward, or in the direction
of, the east.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Eastern</ent>⟦br⟧
